# app

Renders an application scope declaration as an XML context wrapper. The XML boundary signals to the model that everything inside is a scoped architectural context — not a prose description to summarize, but a precise operational boundary to work within.

# entity Input

- directive: 'app'
- name: the application identifier (e.g. 'cartService') — optional
- body: the application's intent, service boundaries, and deployment targets

# entity Output

```markdown
<system_context type="APP"{{#name}} name="{{name}}"{{/name}}>

{{body}}

</system_context>
```

# rule

- name is optional. {{#name}} name="{{name}}"{{/name}} is a conditional block — the name attribute is included only when name is non-empty.
- The closing `</system_context>` tag must always be present and on its own line with a blank line before it.
